VNagaswaram vidwans Sheik Mehaboob Subhani and Kalishabi Mehaboob presented an enchanting nagaswaram concert at the annual music and drama festival conducted by  Sri Rama Gana Sabha Trust, Tiruchi, at Balakala Vidhanam recently.The concert commenced with a varnam, &#8216;Evari Bodha&#8217;  in Abhogi.  The concert was a mix of popular kirtanas of Tyagaraja and sahityams of Tamil scholars and poets. The kirtana, &#8216;Bhajare Manasa&#8217;  set to Adi talam whetted the appetite  of the audience.The sahityam of Muthaiah Bhagavatar, &#8216;Sarasamuka&#8217;  set to Rupaka talam and  an Oothukaadu Venkatasubbiar composition kept the audience interest  alive all through.The audience was thrilled over the meticulous rendition of the saint-poet&#8217;s popular kirtana, &#8216;Marukelara O Raghava&#8217; in Jayanthasri.  It was quickly followed by &#8216;Abimanamu&#8217;.With perfection in laya,  the rendition of &#8216;Rama Neeyada&#8217; in Kharaharapriya  set to Adi talam, was soaked in bhakti bhava.Sri Purandradasa&#8217;s kirtana, &#8216;Jagadhodharana,&#8217; Subramanya Bharati&#8217;s  &#8216;Chinnanchiru Kiliye,&#8217; a ragamalika and a tillana formed the highlight of the concert that concluded with a tillana and Arunagirinathar Tirupugazh.T.V.Muthukumar and P.M.Shankar ably supported the duo on the tavil.  Gopalasamy, Whole Time Director of  Dalmia Cements, was the chief guest  and Visalam Gopalasamy inaugurated the festival.Bottom Template Starts
